# Superpowers + GSD Integration

This project uses **Superpowers** for engineering discipline and **GSD (Get Stuff Done)** for phase-based execution orchestration.

## Superpowers Skills

| Skill | When | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| brainstorming | Before any creative work | Explore options before committing |
| writing-plans | Before implementation | Create step-by-step plan |
| test-driven-development | During implementation | Write tests first, then code |
| requesting-code-review | After completing tasks | Verify quality and correctness |
| verification-before-completion | Before merge | Final check before shipping |
| finishing-a-development-branch | Branch complete | Guide merge/PR process |

## GSD Workflow

Each x.ospec **change** maps to a GSD **phase**:

```
/gsd:plan-phase N    -->  xospec/changes/<change-id>/
  discuss-phase      -->  proposal.md  (Why / Who / What)
  plan-phase         -->  design.md + tasks.md  (How)
  execute-phase      -->  Implementation
  verify             -->  spec delta --> living spec
```

### Key GSD Commands

| Command | Maps to | Purpose |
|---------|---------|---------|
| `/gsd:progress` | — | Check current phase status |
| `/gsd:plan-phase N` | design.md + tasks.md | Create execution plan |
| `/gsd:execute-phase N` | Implementation | Execute with atomic commits |
| `/gsd:next` | — | Auto-advance to next step |

## File Locations

- **Superpowers skills:** Installed in your AI agent (Claude Code, Cursor, etc.)
- **GSD state:** `.planning/STATE.md`
- **GSD roadmap:** `.planning/ROADMAP.md`
- **x.ospec specs:** `xospec/specs/`
- **x.ospec changes:** `xospec/changes/`

## Setup

1. Install Superpowers in your agent
2. GSD commands are available via Superpowers skill system
3. Skills activate automatically based on context
